      </section-body></informative-references></references><glossary-of-terms><section-title>Glossary of terms</section-title><section-body>
      <paragraph-text type="preamble">In this place, the following terms or expressions are used with the meaning indicated:</paragraph-text><table>
         <table-row>
            <table-column>
               <paragraph-text type="body">Incandescent</paragraph-text>
            </table-column>
            <table-column>
               <paragraph-text type="body">Capable of emitting visible light when heated.</paragraph-text>
            </table-column>
         </table-row>
         <table-row>
            <table-column>
               <paragraph-text type="body">Incandescent mantle</paragraph-text>
            </table-column>
            <table-column>
               <paragraph-text type="body">A device comprising a lace-like hood or envelope of thin, porous, refractory material that glows when it is positioned in a flame or otherwise heated by combustion of a distinct combustible material.</paragraph-text>
            </table-column>
         </table-row>
         <table-row>
            <table-column>
               <paragraph-text type="body">Light source</paragraph-text>
            </table-column>
            <table-column>
               <paragraph-text type="body">The entity (e.g. mantle) that generates light for a lighting device or apparatus.</paragraph-text>
            </table-column>
         </table-row>
      </table>
      </section-body></glossary-of-terms></definition-item>
